headline: Looking Ahead to the Q2 Earnings Season
summary: While the revisions trend has notably stabilized in recent weeks, the magnitude of cuts to 2025 Q2 estimates since the start of the period is larger and more widespread compared to what we have become accustomed to seeing in the post-COVID period.

headline: Corrections & Amplifications
summary: A Business & Finance article on Monday about job-applicant tracking systems incorrectly implied it started after the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks.  Walgreens Boots Alliance reported a net loss of $175 million for its latest quarter.  In some editions Friday, a What’s News item and display text for a Business & Finance article about the drugstore chain incorrectly said losses narrowed.

headline: The Score: Bumble, Tesla, Shell and More Stocks That Defined the Week
summary: Per a regulatory filing, Bumble expects the cuts to generate up to $40 million in annual savings.  Chief Executive  Whitney Wolfe Herd —who returned to the company in March—told employees in a letter Wednesday that she hopes the cuts make the company “more agile.”
